main event: Radar beacon returns with no known or identifiable source have been noted by the Guam FAA controllers since October 1962.
interesting points: The objects were detected on radar at various ranges, usually 50 to 70 miles northwest of Andersen AFB, and remained on the radar scope for up to 30 minutes, averaging over 10 minutes.
Airborne radar contact was made on one date, June 27, 1964, using the AS-59 system.
The targets appeared to be of an electrical nature only, with no visual sightings made except for a reported cloud on June 27.
The sightings occurred at various times of day and night, with most happening at night.
FAA air traffic controllers, considered highly qualified and reliable observers, have witnessed this phenomenon.
sighted object: Radar beacon returns with no known or identifiable source
